content:
if you're already late,
chill out. no point in
rushing now.

if you hate your job,
find a new one, then
quit. in that order.

if someone says,
"i technically didn't,"
they did.

if you can barely walk,
there’s no way you
can drive.

if they’ve said,
“new year, new me,”
for the past three years,
don’t trust them.

if someone goes,
“wait for it...”
wait for it.

four words to live by:
always hungry;
never thirsty.
